==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[moveable]]

===Adjective===
'''movable'''
# Capable of being [[move]]d, [[lift]]ed, [[carry|carried]], [[draw]]n, [[turn]]ed, or [[convey]]ed, or in any way made to change [[place]] or [[posture]]; [[susceptible]] of [[motion]]; not [[fixed]] or [[stationary]]; as, a movable steam engine.
# Changing from one [[time]] to another; as, movable feasts, i. e., [[church festival]]s, the date of which varies from year to year.

====Antonyms====
* [[immovable]]

====Derived terms====
* [[movable letter]]

===Noun===
'''movable'''
# Something which is movable; an article of [[wares]] or [[goods]]; a [[commodity]]; a piece of [[property]] not fixed, or not a part of [[real estate]]; generally, in the plural, goods; wares; [[furniture]].

